<br>A 37-year-old man from Phu Yen Province in south-central Vietnam<br>rec=
ently did not survive after getting bitten by a strange dog over 3<br>month=
s ago, notwithstanding receiving hospital attention for symptoms<br>of rabi=
es. Nguyen Gia Phong, chairman of Hoa Vinh Ward in Dong Hoa<br>Town, Phu Ye=
n, where 37-year-old [NTK] lived, confirmed his death,<br>allegedly due to =
rabies, on Wednesday [10 Jan 2024].=0D<br>=0D<br>According to a report from=
 the Dong Hoa Medical Center, [NTK]<br>sustained a dog bite on his hand fro=
m an unidentified dog over 3<br>months ago. At the time, he perceived the i=
njury as a mere scratch<br>from the animal's collar and did not seek vaccin=
ation against rabies.=0D<br>=0D<br>On 4 Jan 2024, [NTK] showed symptoms of =
difficulty breathing, chest<br>tightness, and vomiting before developing a =
fear of water and<br>tiredness 4 days later [8 Jan 2024]. His family took h=
im to Phu Yen<br>General Hospital at 0:00 on Tuesday [9 Jan 2024] before tr=
ansferring<br>the man to Khanh Hoa Hospital for Tropical Diseases in neighb=
oring<br>Khanh Hoa Province.=0D<br>=0D<br>The patient could not make it by =
2:00 am on Wednesday [10 Jan 2024].<br>All individuals in close contact wit=
h [NTK] were then vaccinated<br>against rabies.=0D<br>=0D<br>Nguyen Dong, d=
irector of the Khanh Hoa Hospital for Tropical Diseases,<br>stated that [NT=
K] was brought to the hospital too late, as the rabies<br>had already progr=
essed to a stage beyond treatment.=0D<br>=0D<br>"Dying from rabies is often=
 a result of failure to seek timely<br>vaccination after a dog bite," Dong =
explained. "People tend to delay<br>until the onset of a rabies attack, but=
 by then, it's too late as the<br>virus has attacked the brain. There's no =
cure once the disease<br>manifests itself."=0D<br>=0D<br>Huynh Le Xuan Bich=
, deputy director of the Department of Health of Phu<br>Yen Province, empha=
sized that immediate action is crucial in case of a<br>dog bite. Bich advis=
ed cleaning the wound with water and soap, seeking<br>prompt examination, c=
onsultation, and receiving rabies vaccinations<br>and/or anti-rabies serum =
to avoid unnecessary risks.=0D<br>=0D<br>[Byline: Bao Anh, Nguyen Hoang, Mi=
